    Scope and Contents
Morton discusses her education abroad; Oberlin College and the University of Chicago; race relations; NAACP housing issues in Indiana; school integration; women's roles and issues; peace movements; and war tax resistance. 2 tapes, 180 mins. 
Interview by Peggy Boyer, 1986 
